name: FFF Stop
description:
Every stencil has it's day - last application of FFF. Painted on everyone's favourite paper (and why not?). Edition of two, framed.

Spraypaint on Printed Paper.
19" W x 28" H x 2" D

name: Smoking Kills
description:
Satisfying our Camel crush. Four colour, hand-cut stencil with a semigloss finish. Will hang vertical or horizontal.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
48" W x 8" H x 2" D

name: Black on Black
description:
Another hand-cut stencil on painted card shadow box mounted in an up-cycled (newly fluorescent) frame. Ready to hang. 


Mixed Media. Framed
10" W x 8" H

name: Cold Hands
description:
A mysterious figure from beyond the wall. Original pencil and ink drawing on a heavy grey card. Signed by the artist. 

Pencil and Ink. Framed. 
23" W x 30" H

name: DPWF
description:
Don't play with fire or at least your Swan Vestas. Four colour, hand-cut stencil with a semigloss finish. Ready to hang.

Spraypaint on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D

name: Exhibit A
description:
Previously enjoyed spraycan nozzles displayed in a custom mahogany case. Each nozzle is individually mounted on an entomology pin. Save a butterfly, display a nozzle.

Mixed Media. 12 Pieces. Framed. 
12" W x 10" H x 2.5" D

name: Dungeoness
description:
This wreck of a boat was abandoned on the shingle at Dungeoness in Kent. A curious and protected landscape that is bleak, beautiful and by nature, always changing.

Oil and Acrylic on Canvas.
24" W x 36" H x 1.5"D

name: Alphabet
description:
A floriated and ornamented alphabet originated and provided by Anita Gohil. Letters are laser-etched cheery veneer over mahogany. The custom black mahogany display box is felt lined. Only two made (and one belongs to Anita).

Mixed Media. 26 Pieces. Framed.
14" W x 20" H x 2.5" D

name: Let Me Hear You
description:
A faithful recreation of a popular classic by Edward Munch lovingly re-pasteled onto a skateboard. Skateboards are made by humans with wood from trees.

Pastel on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D

name: The Bison
description:
A two colour, hand-pulled, screen print on natural, 300gsm archival paper. Signed and numbered by the artist. Edition of 10.

Silkscreen Print on Archival Paper.
22.5" W x 30.5" H

name: Defense de Fumer
description:
The original Captain Zig Zag maybe burnt out, but he's still smoking. Four colour, hand-cut stencil with a semigloss finish. Ready to hang.

Spraypaint on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D

name: Carp Dieme
description:
Unlike the real thing, these carp don't need any looking after. Lots of relief, detail, lovely strokes and bright colours make it a piece you can enjoy close-up and from afar. 

Oil and Acrylic on Canvas.
40" W x 40" H x 1.5" D

name: Three Sisters
description:
Three Sisters is a mountain range synonymous with Canmore, Alberta. This drawing is actually derived from an old photo collection we have in the studio (in case anyone is wondering).

Pencil on Paper.
30" W x 24" H

name: Horse Business
description:
Produced during the 2012 Calgary Stampede, this hand-sculptured and kilned horse means business. Can be enjoyed but cannot be ridden. 

This item is super heavy and will require special delivery so ideally it will find a local home!

Hand-fired Clay Sculpture.
24" W x 21" H x 11" D

name: Two Tribes
description:
A set of two hand-painted skateboards - one's a he, the other's a she. On display at Without Papers Pizza in Inglewood, Calgary.

Acrylic on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D

name: UU
description:
More blanks to fill in. One colour, hand cut stencil.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
12" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: Elk Stag
description:
An icon of the north and popular resident of our nearest national park. Elk stags are magnificent to see in real life and just as much fun to paint. The kick tail longboard is made from Canadian Maple.

Acrylic on Wood Longboard.
10" W x 42.5" H

name: J is for January
description:
J is also for June and July but we'll figure that out later in the year. First in a series of 12 mixed media pieces.

Acrylic on Wood Panel.
12" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: Ugly People
description:
Dr Phil might suggest looking at these mugs everyday may make you'll feel better about your own.

Ink and Acrylic on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D

name: The Queen
description:
Stencil portraits of Queen Elizabeth II. Painted and produced in 2011. One original (Bettertimes Burgundy) remaining. Custom editions or colours on request - the stencil is still good for another run.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
16" W x 20" H x 2" D

name: Hare
description:
Signed and numbered by the artist. Edition of 25.


Giclee on Canvas.
13.5" W x 16.5" H

name: Network Southeast
description:
No two journeys are the same. Signed and numbered by the artist. Edition of 5.

Giclee on Canvas.
11" W x 14" H

name: Supermarket
description:
Dean likes zombies. Zombies like supermarkets. Supermarkets like zombies. Now you have all the facts. Signed and numbered by the artist. Edition of 10.

Giclee on Canvas.
17" W x 13" H

name: Return of the Bison
description:
A two colour, hand-pulled, screen print on natural, 300gsm archival paper. Signed and numbered by the artist. Edition of 10.

Silkscreen Print on Archival Paper.
00" W x 00" H

name: PMS Chip Set
description:
A set of four chips (205, 548, 7710 and 7745) from our very first batch. All made with NBL - nothing but love. 

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
48" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: PMS Chips Mk 1
description:
After some trial and error we were able to get quite the chip production line going. Everyone handmade and all the colours are accurate. Available individually but work really nice in sets.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
12" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: Fluorescent Hybrid
description:
If you have a really boring wall this may be the piece for you.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
12" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: FFF
description:
Fill in the blanks. All we needed was some hand-cut stencils, spray cans and a copy of a good book called The Dictionary.

Spraypaint on Wood Panel.
12" W x 16" H x 2" D

name: Russian Dolls
description:
Hand-painted set of russian (or to be correct, matryoshka) dolls in bubble gum colour combinations. Custom orders available on request.

Spraypaint on Wood.
6" H x 4" W x 4" D.

name: Sold Out
description:
This piece has been finely-crafted from leftovers of paint and stencils. No expense spared.

Spraypaint on Wood Skateboard.
7.5" W x 31" H x 1.5" D
